---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'quick-verdict', text: 'Quick Verdict', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Side-by-Side Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'cigna', text: 'Cigna Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'bupa', text: 'Bupa Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'aetna', text: 'Aetna International', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pacific-details', text: 'Pacific Region Details', level: 2 },
  { id: 'best-for', text: 'Which Is Best For You?', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { href: '/countries/australia/insurance', text: 'Australia Insurance Guide' },
  { href: '/countries/new-zealand/insurance', text: 'New Zealand Insurance' },
  { href: '/best/expat-health-insurance', text: 'Best Expat Insurance' },
  { href: '/providers/cigna-global', text: 'Cigna Global Review' },
  { href: '/providers/bupa-global', text: 'Bupa Global Review' },
];

const mainComparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'bupa', header: 'Bupa Global' },
  { key: 'aetna', header: 'Aetna International' },
];

const mainComparisonRows = [
  { feature: 'Australia Network', cigna: 'Extensive', bupa: 'Very strong (local presence)', aetna: 'Good' },
  { feature: 'New Zealand Network', cigna: 'Good', bupa: 'Strong', aetna: 'Moderate' },
  { feature: 'Pacific Islands Coverage', cigna: 'Direct billing limited', bupa: 'Direct billing available', aetna: 'Reimbursement mostly' },
  { feature: 'Medical Evacuation', cigna: 'Yes (to regional hub)', bupa: 'Yes (to Australia/NZ)', aetna: 'Yes' },
  { feature: 'Remote Area Coverage', cigna: 'Yes with evacuation', bupa: 'Yes with evacuation', aetna: 'Yes with evacuation' },
  { feature: 'Medicare Integration (AU)', cigna: 'Coordinates well', bupa: 'Strong integration', aetna: 'Coordinates' },
  { feature: 'Annual Maximum', cigna: 'Unlimited', bupa: 'Unlimited', aetna: '$8M' },
  { feature: 'Local Service Team', cigna: 'Regional office', bupa: 'Australian HQ', aetna: 'Regional support' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'profile', header: 'Profile' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'bupa', header: 'Bupa Global' },
  { key: 'aetna', header: 'Aetna International' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { profile: 'Individual (35, Australia)', cigna: '$380/mo', bupa: '$420/mo', aetna: '$340/mo' },
  { profile: 'Individual (35, NZ)', cigna: '$350/mo', bupa: '$380/mo', aetna: '$320/mo' },
  { profile: 'Couple (40s, Australia)', cigna: '$720/mo', bupa: '$800/mo', aetna: '$650/mo' },
  { profile: 'Pacific Islands based', cigna: '$400/mo', bupa: '$440/mo', aetna: '$360/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Cigna vs Bupa vs Aetna for Pacific/Australia | 2025 Comparison"
  description="Compare Cigna Global, Bupa Global, and Aetna International for Australia, New Zealand, and Pacific Islands. Expert analysis of regional networks, evacuation services, and local integration."
  headline="Cigna vs Bupa vs Aetna: Pacific & Australia"
  subheadline="Complete comparison for expats in Australia, New Zealand, and Pacific Islands—covering regional networks, Medicare integration, evacuation services, and remote area coverage."
  heroImage="/images/pages/provider-card-generic.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes"
  ctaButtonHref="/get-quotes"
>
  <section id="quick-verdict" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Quick Verdict</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-primary-800 mb-2">Cigna Global</h3>
        <p class="text-primary-700 mb-3">Best Overall</p>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-4">Excellent Australia/NZ coverage with unlimited benefits. Strong regional presence and reliable evacuation services for remote Pacific locations.</p>
        <a href="/providers/cigna-global" class="inline-block bg-primary-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded hover:bg-primary-700 transition text-sm" style="color: white !important;">Learn More</a>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-purple-50 border border-purple-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-purple-800 mb-2">Bupa Global</h3>
        <p class="text-purple-700 mb-3">Best Local Presence</p>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-4">Australian headquarters means the strongest local network and support. Excellent Medicare coordination and Pacific Islands direct billing.</p>
        <a href="/providers/bupa-global" class="inline-block bg-purple-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded hover:bg-purple-700 transition text-sm" style="color: white !important;">Learn More</a>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-green-800 mb-2">Aetna International</h3>
        <p class="text-green-700 mb-3">Best Value</p>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-4">Competitive pricing for Australia/NZ with solid coverage. Good option if you don't need Pacific Islands direct billing.</p>
        <a href="/providers/aetna-international" class="inline-block bg-green-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded hover:bg-green-700 transition text-sm" style="color: white !important;">Learn More</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="comparison-table" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Side-by-Side Comparison</h2>
    <ComparisonTable columns={mainComparisonColumns} rows={mainComparisonRows} />
  </section>

  <section id="cigna" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Cigna Global</h2>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
      <span class="bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Australia/NZ Strong</span>
      <span class="bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Unlimited Coverage</span>
      <span class="bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Evacuation Services</span>
    </div>

    <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">Cigna Global maintains an extensive network across Australia and New Zealand with direct billing at major hospitals and specialists. For expats in Sydney, Melbourne, Auckland, or other major cities, accessing quality care is straightforward. The network includes public and private hospitals, giving flexibility in care choices.</p>

    <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">For Pacific Islands coverage, Cigna provides strong emergency care and evacuation services. While direct billing on smaller islands is limited, the evacuation to Australian or New Zealand hospitals is well-coordinated. Regional offices understand Pacific logistics, and claims processing for island-based care is experienced and efficient.</p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-green-800 mb-2">Pacific Strengths</h4>
        <ul class="text-green-700 text-sm space-y-1">
          <li>• Extensive AU/NZ network</li>
          <li>• Unlimited coverage</li>
          <li>• Strong evacuation services</li>
          <li>• Regional expertise</li>
          <li>• Public/private hospital access</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-amber-800 mb-2">Considerations</h4>
        <ul class="text-amber-700 text-sm space-y-1">
          <li>• Limited Pacific Islands direct billing</li>
          <li>• Higher premium than Aetna</li>
          <li>• No Australian HQ</li>
          <li>• Some claims reimbursement needed</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <a href="/providers/cigna-global" class="inline-block bg-primary-600 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
  </section>

  <section id="bupa" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Bupa Global</h2>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
      <span class="bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Australian HQ</span>
      <span class="bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Medicare Integration</span>
      <span class="bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Pacific Direct Billing</span>
    </div>

    <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">Bupa Global has its Asia-Pacific headquarters in Australia, translating to the strongest local network and support. The Australian network is unmatched—virtually every major hospital and specialist participates, with seamless direct billing. Coordination with Medicare is smooth for those who qualify, maximizing coverage while minimizing gaps.</p>

    <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">For Pacific Islands, Bupa has invested in direct billing relationships with major facilities in Fiji, Papua New Guinea, and other larger island nations. While smaller islands still require evacuation for serious care, day-to-day medical needs can often be handled locally without upfront payment. The Australian base means quick evacuation coordination when needed.</p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-green-800 mb-2">Pacific Strengths</h4>
        <ul class="text-green-700 text-sm space-y-1">
          <li>• Australian headquarters</li>
          <li>• Best local network</li>
          <li>• Medicare coordination</li>
          <li>• Pacific direct billing</li>
          <li>• Fast evacuation from AU base</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-amber-800 mb-2">Considerations</h4>
        <ul class="text-amber-700 text-sm space-y-1">
          <li>• Highest premium in region</li>
          <li>• Remote islands still limited</li>
          <li>• Premium service = premium price</li>
          <li>• May be excessive for simple needs</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <a href="/providers/bupa-global" class="inline-block bg-purple-600 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-purple-700 transition font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Bupa Quote</a>
  </section>

  <section id="aetna" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Aetna International</h2>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
      <span class="bg-green-100 text-green-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Competitive Pricing</span>
      <span class="bg-green-100 text-green-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">AU/NZ Coverage</span>
      <span class="bg-green-100 text-green-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">US Connection</span>
    </div>

    <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">Aetna International offers solid Australia and New Zealand coverage at the most competitive pricing of the three. The network covers major hospitals and most specialists in capital cities, with good direct billing coverage. For expats primarily based in urban Australia or New Zealand, Aetna provides comprehensive care at lower cost.</p>

    <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">Pacific Islands coverage is more limited—primarily reimbursement-based with evacuation services for serious conditions. If you're occasionally traveling to Pacific Islands but based in Australia/NZ, this works fine. For those living primarily in Pacific Island nations, Bupa's direct billing network is more practical.</p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-green-800 mb-2">Pacific Strengths</h4>
        <ul class="text-green-700 text-sm space-y-1">
          <li>• Lowest regional pricing</li>
          <li>• Good AU/NZ network</li>
          <li>• Strong evacuation coverage</li>
          <li>• CVS Health backing</li>
          <li>• US coverage if needed</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-amber-800 mb-2">Considerations</h4>
        <ul class="text-amber-700 text-sm space-y-1">
          <li>• Pacific Islands mostly reimbursement</li>
          <li>• Network smaller than Bupa</li>
          <li>• $8M cap (vs unlimited)</li>
          <li>• Less local presence</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <a href="/providers/aetna-international" class="inline-block bg-green-600 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-green-700 transition font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Aetna Quote</a>
  </section>

  <CTABox
    title="Get Pacific Region Quotes"
    description="Compare coverage and pricing for Australia, New Zealand, and Pacific Islands locations."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/get-quotes"
  />

  <section id="pricing" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Pricing Comparison</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-6">Monthly premiums for Pacific region coverage:</p>
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mt-4">*Pricing is indicative for comprehensive inpatient + outpatient coverage. Australia typically costs more due to higher healthcare costs. Actual premiums depend on age, health history, and specific plan chosen.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="pacific-details" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Pacific Region Details</h2>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Australia</h3>
        <ul class="text-neutral-700 text-sm space-y-2">
          <li>• Medicare available if resident</li>
          <li>• Private coverage complements Medicare</li>
          <li>• Skip public wait times</li>
          <li>• Access private hospitals</li>
          <li>• Tax benefits for private cover</li>
          <li>• All providers have strong networks</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-3">New Zealand</h3>
        <ul class="text-neutral-700 text-sm space-y-2">
          <li>• Public system covers accidents (ACC)</li>
          <li>• Private cover for elective/non-accident</li>
          <li>• Good provider networks</li>
          <li>• Lower costs than Australia</li>
          <li>• Auckland/Wellington well-covered</li>
          <li>• Regional access varies</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-800 mb-3">Pacific Islands Healthcare</h3>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-bold text-blue-800 mb-2">Larger Islands</h4>
          <ul class="text-blue-700 text-sm space-y-1">
            <li>• Fiji: Good private hospitals</li>
            <li>• Papua New Guinea: Major cities</li>
            <li>• Tahiti: French system</li>
            <li>• Guam: US-style care</li>
            <li>• Direct billing more available</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-bold text-blue-800 mb-2">Smaller Islands</h4>
          <ul class="text-blue-700 text-sm space-y-1">
            <li>• Tonga: Basic facilities</li>
            <li>• Samoa: Limited hospitals</li>
            <li>• Vanuatu: Evacuation often needed</li>
            <li>• Evacuation to NZ/Australia</li>
            <li>• Reimbursement common</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-bold text-blue-800 mb-2">Remote Areas</h4>
          <ul class="text-blue-700 text-sm space-y-1">
            <li>• Air evacuation essential</li>
            <li>• Plan for travel to care</li>
            <li>• Emergency only locally</li>
            <li>• Keep supplies available</li>
            <li>• Know evacuation process</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="best-for" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Which Is Best For You?</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="bg-primary-50 border-l-4 border-primary-600 p-4">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-primary-800 mb-2">Choose Cigna Global if:</h3>
        <ul class="text-primary-700 space-y-1">
          <li>• You want excellent AU/NZ coverage with global benefits</li>
          <li>• Unlimited coverage matters</li>
          <li>• Pacific Islands are occasional travel</li>
          <li>• Reliable evacuation services are important</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-l-4 border-purple-600 p-4">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-purple-800 mb-2">Choose Bupa Global if:</h3>
        <ul class="text-purple-700 space-y-1">
          <li>• Australia is your primary base</li>
          <li>• Best local network matters most</li>
          <li>• Medicare coordination is valuable</li>
          <li>• Pacific Islands direct billing is needed</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-green-50 border-l-4 border-green-600 p-4">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-green-800 mb-2">Choose Aetna International if:</h3>
        <ul class="text-green-700 space-y-1">
          <li>• Budget is a priority</li>
          <li>• AU/NZ urban areas are your base</li>
          <li>• Pacific Islands aren't frequent</li>
          <li>• US coverage connection is valuable</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="faqs" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-2">Do I need private insurance if I have Medicare in Australia?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">Medicare covers public hospitals and many services, but private insurance provides choice of doctor, skip public wait lists, private room, and extras like dental/optical. For serious conditions, private cover means faster treatment. Most expats who qualify for Medicare still maintain private coverage for flexibility and speed.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-2">How does evacuation work from Pacific Islands?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">For serious conditions, insurers arrange air ambulance or commercial medical flights to Australia or New Zealand. Costs can exceed $50,000—covered by your policy. Stabilization happens locally, then evacuation to definitive care. All three insurers have 24/7 coordination centers experienced with Pacific evacuations.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-2">What about coverage in remote Australian outback?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">All three insurers cover Royal Flying Doctor Service evacuations from remote areas. Emergency care is covered wherever you are; the evacuation gets you to appropriate facilities. If you're frequently in remote areas, ensure your plan explicitly includes air ambulance and emergency evacuation with adequate limits.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-2">Can I see any doctor in Australia/NZ with these plans?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">Yes, but direct billing varies. Network providers mean you pay nothing upfront. Out-of-network providers require you to pay and submit claims for reimbursement. Bupa's network is largest in Australia; all three have good networks in major cities. Check network coverage in your specific city before choosing.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="bg-neutral-100 rounded-lg p-6 text-sm text-neutral-600">
    <p><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Pacific region coverage, networks, and evacuation arrangements vary by specific plan and change over time. This comparison represents typical regional coverage—actual options depend on your specific location, plan choice, and insurer negotiations. Always confirm Pacific Islands coverage and evacuation terms before enrolling, especially for remote locations.</p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
